    <main>
      <div class="page-header">
        <p class="breadcrumb"><a href="games.html">games</a> // builder &amp; sim</p>
        <h1>Builder &amp; Sim</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Cities, farms, truck routes, theme parks. The meditative art of systems thinking — and watching it all burn when the traffic backs up.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- CIV SERIES -->
      <div class="mini-cat">
        <p class="mini-cat-label">// series</p>
        <p class="mini-cat-title">Civilization</p>
        <p class="mini-cat-desc">One more turn. The most dangerous words in gaming — courtesy of Sid Meier since 1991.</p>

        <div class="game-grid" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(160px, 1fr))">
          <div class="game-card"><div class="game-card-inner">
            <div class="cover-wrap"><div class="cover-placeholder">Civilization V</div></div>
            <span class="cover-caption">Hex grid. One city challenge.</span>
            <p class="game-title">Civilization V</p>
            <p class="game-year">2010</p>
            <p class="star-rating">★★★★★</p>
            <p class="game-blurb">The refinement. Hex tiles, one-unit-per-tile, Brave New World. Still the most-played Civ for a reason — nearly perfect after expansions.</p>
          </div></div>

          <div class="game-card"><div class="game-card-inner">
            <div class="cover-wrap"><div class="cover-placeholder">Civilization VI</div></div>
            <span class="cover-caption">Districts. Unstacking cities.</span>
            <p class="game-title">Civilization VI</p>
            <p class="game-year">2016</p>
            <p class="star-rating">★★★★☆</p>
            <p class="game-blurb">District system revolutionized city planning. Governors, GS and R&F expansions. Different from V but comparably great in its own lane.</p>
          </div></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- TRUCK SIM SERIES -->
      <div class="mini-cat">
        <p class="mini-cat-label">// series</p>
        <p class="mini-cat-title">Truck Simulators</p>
        <p class="mini-cat-desc">SCS Software built a genre. Hauling freight across Europe and America at 60mph is strangely one of the most relaxing experiences in gaming.</p>

        <table class="series-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Title</th><th>Year</th><th>Rating</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Euro Truck Simulator 2</td>
              <td><span class="year-badge">2012</span></td>
              <td><span class="rating-cell">★★★★★</span></td>
              <td class="note-cell">The original. Haul freight across Europe, build your company, mod endlessly. Thirteen years of updates — still the definitive trucking game.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>American Truck Simulator</td>
              <td><span class="year-badge">2016</span></td>
              <td><span class="rating-cell">★★★★★</span></td>
              <td class="note-cell">The American highway romance made interactive. Coast to coast expansion states, CB radio chatter, big rigs through Monument Valley at dusk.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p class="section-divider">// the rest of the collection — chronological order</p>

      <div class="game-grid">

        <div class="game-card"><div class="game-card-inner">
          <div class="cover-wrap"><div class="cover-placeholder">Cities:<br/>Skylines</div></div>
          <span class="cover-caption">The SimCity successor we needed</span>
          <p class="game-title">Cities: Skylines</p>
          <p class="game-year">2015</p>
          <p class="star-rating">★★★★★</p>
          <p class="game-blurb">Saved the city builder genre when EA dropped the ball. Mods, traffic management, zoning theory — a graduate course in urban planning disguised as a game.</p>
        </div></div>

        <div class="game-card"><div class="game-card-inner">
          <div class="cover-wrap"><div class="cover-placeholder">Planet Coaster</div></div>
          <span class="cover-caption">Theme park builder from RCT veterans</span>
          <p class="game-title">Planet Coaster</p>
          <p class="game-year">2016</p>
          <p class="star-rating">★★★★★</p>
          <p class="game-blurb">Frontier Developments gave RCT fans the spiritual successor they'd waited a decade for. Creative freedom off the charts. The coaster physics alone could eat a weekend.</p>
        </div></div>

        <div class="game-card"><div class="game-card-inner">
          <div class="cover-wrap"><div class="cover-placeholder">House Flipper</div></div>
          <span class="cover-caption">Buy. Gut. Renovate. Sell.</span>
          <p class="game-title">House Flipper</p>
          <p class="game-year">2018</p>
          <p class="star-rating">★★★☆☆</p>
          <p class="game-blurb">Oddly therapeutic. Mopping floors, painting walls, laying tile. A game that rewards the same part of your brain as a clean kitchen. Deeply cozy.</p>
        </div></div>

        <div class="game-card"><div class="game-card-inner">
          <div class="cover-wrap"><div class="cover-placeholder">Planet Zoo</div></div>
          <span class="cover-caption">Build the habitat. Feed the giraffe.</span>
          <p class="game-title">Planet Zoo</p>
          <p class="game-year">2019</p>
          <p class="star-rating">★★★★★</p>
          <p class="game-blurb">Planet Coaster but for zoology obsessives. Animal welfare mechanics, habitat design, species behavior. More depth than any zoo game has the right to have.</p>
        </div></div>

        <div class="game-card"><div class="game-card-inner">
          <div class="cover-wrap"><div class="cover-placeholder">Transport<br/>Fever 2</div></div>
          <span class="cover-caption">Rail, road, air, sea — all of it</span>
          <p class="game-title">Transport Fever 2</p>
          <p class="game-year">2019</p>
          <p class="star-rating">★★★★☆</p>
          <p class="game-blurb">Build transport empires spanning continents. Watches cities grow in response to your rail lines. The supply chain brain gets fed generously here.</p>
        </div></div>

        <div class="game-card"><div class="game-card-inner">
          <div class="cover-wrap"><div class="cover-placeholder">PowerWash<br/>Simulator</div></div>
          <span class="cover-caption">The ASMR of video games</span>
          <p class="game-title">PowerWash Simulator</p>
          <p class="game-year">2022</p>
          <p class="star-rating">★★★★☆</p>
          <p class="game-blurb">Point hose. Remove grime. Watch progress bar fill. Sounds boring — is completely hypnotic. The only game that genuinely relaxes your nervous system.</p>
        </div></div>

      </div>
    </main>
  </div>

  <footer>© 2026 — Cairo Yepez · Chicago, IL · All rights reserved · A tribute to fallen heroes of the era.</footer>

  <script>
    document.querySelectorAll('.game-card').forEach(card => {
      const inner = card.querySelector('.game-card-inner');
      card.addEventListener('mousemove', e => {
        const r = card.getBoundingClientRect();
        const x = e.clientX - r.left - r.width / 2;
        const y = e.clientY - r.top - r.height / 2;
        inner.style.transform = `rotateX(${-(y/r.height)*18}deg) rotateY(${(x/r.width)*18}deg) scale(1.04)`;
      });
      card.addEventListener('mouseleave', () => { inner.style.transition = 'transform .4s ease'; inner.style.transform = 'rotateX(0) rotateY(0) scale(1)'; });
      card.addEventListener('mouseenter', () => { inner.style.transition = 'transform .1s ease'; });
    });
  </script>

